          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The thermal flux which is available well back in the",
                "graphite block, using the cyclotron as a neutron",
                "source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The number of fast neutrons given off was measured by",
                "making a volume integral of the resonance activity",
                "acquired by indium foils and comparing this with a",
                "similar integral from a Ra-Be source of known output;",
                "the number of fissions was measured by counting the",
                "fissions from a thin foil on the face of a case",
                "containing the sample of fissionable material, and",
                "knowing the ratio of weights of material in the foil",
                "to material in the sample. The measurement gives a",
                "rather accurate value of the ratio nubar/Q where Q is",
                "the neutron output of Ra-Be source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The self absorption correction was calculated on the",
                "basis of this average counting rate plus the",
                "assumption of an isotropic neutron flux around the",
                "sample. The straight-through self-absorption in the",
                "sample was about 11 percent in the worst case (round",
                "25 sample); it becomes larger when averaged over all",
                "angles, but is partially monitored by the detector",
                "foil, one side of which is shaded by the sample. The",
                "net correction was 5 percent for the round 25 sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Compiler's comment: Los Alamos notation uses 49 for",
                "Z=94, A=239 (239Pu) and 25 for Z=92, A=235 (235U)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "date": 19760804,
                "history": "T"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Translated from SCISRS."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "date": 19820519,
                "history": "A"
              },
              "free_text": [
